<td class='main'><div class="main">

<center><h1>Emotion</h1></center>

<p></p>

<span class="contentmain"><br />


<p>
Emotion is an Evas smart-object library providing video capabilities.  Emotion leverages

<a href="http://xinehq.de/">libxine 1.0</a> and integrates seemlessly with the rest of the EFL.  Because its based
on libxine, any format that it supports (Theora, DiVX, MPEG2, etc) is avalible using Emotion.
</p>

<p>
To demonstrate just how simple Emotion is to use, please look at this DVD player written in 18 lines of C.
</p>

<div class="fragment">
<pre>#include &lt;Evas.h&gt;
#include &lt;Ecore.h&gt;
#include &lt;Ecore_Evas.h&gt;
#include &lt;Emotion.h&gt;

Evas_Object *video;

/* the main function of the program */
int main(int argc, char **argv) {
   Ecore_Evas *ee;

   /* create a canvas, display it, set  */
   ecore_evas_init();
   ee = ecore_evas_software_x11_new(NULL, 0, 0, 0, 800, 600);
   ecore_evas_show(ee);

   /* create a video object */
   video = emotion_object_add(ecore_evas_get(ee));
   emotion_object_file_set(video, "dvd:/");
   emotion_object_play_set(video, 1);
   evas_object_resize(video, 800, 600);
   evas_object_show(video);

   /* run the main loop of the program - playing, drawing, handling events */
   ecore_main_loop_begin();
   
   /* if we exit the main loop we will shut down */
   ecore_evas_shutdown();
   return 0;
}</pre>
</div>

<p>
With Emotion it's unbelievably easy to add video to your application, and by leveraging the rest of the EFL to
build more powerful video players than seen anywhere else.
</p>

<p class="manager">Emotion's project manager is <a target="_self" class="lite" href="http://enlightenment.sourceforge.net/Main/The_Team/">Carsten &quot;Rasterman&quot; Haitzler</a>.</p></span>

</div></td>
